Purchase options and add-ons

  • Help protect your home inside and out with Blink Outdoor 4, Wired Floodlight Camera, and Video Doorbell.
  • See and speak from the Blink app — Experience 1080p HD live view, infrared night vision, and crisp two-way audio.
  • Two-year battery life — Set up yourself in minutes and get up to two years of power on your Outdoor 4 cameras and Video Doorbell with the included AA lithium batteries.
  • Motion detection alerts — Be alerted to motion and customize motion zones from your phone. Even set lights on Wired Floodlight Camera to trigger from the Blink Home Monitor app.
  • Person detection —With Outdoor 4 and Wired Floodlight Camera, get alerts when a person is detected with embedded computer vision (CV) as part of an optional Blink Subscription Plan (sold separately).
  • Save and share clips — Choose to store events in the cloud with a free 30-day trial of the Blink Subscription Plan or locally with the Sync Module 2 (included) plus a USB drive (sold separately).
  • Works with Alexa — Connect to an Alexa-enabled device to engage live view, arm and disarm your system, and more using your voice.
  • Includes four Outdoor 4 cameras, one Wired Floodlight Camera, one Video Doorbell, one Sync Module 2, six mounting kits, 10 AA batteries, 1 USB cable, and 1 power adapter.

We want you to know

To save and share clips, choose from an optional Blink Subscription Plan (sold separately) or store locally with a Blink Sync Module (included) and USB flash drive (sold separately).

Outdoor 4 is not compatible with accessories designed for Outdoor 3rd Gen including Blink Floodlight Mount and Blink Solar Panel Charging Mount.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    4.0 out of 5 stars Economic home security during sales events
    Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2024
    Verified Purchase
    I got the set for a decent price during a sales event on Amazon. I have had the cameras for almost 2 months. The video quality is not as great as I'd like but works for what I need. Zooming in on video feed is nice but not very useful with the lack of video quality. I'm not a big fan of the delay for video recording during motion activation. But luckily haven't missed anything of importance yet. I just hope I don't miss an important event should something happen. I'm sure activation can improve with updates. Batteries on cameras and doorbell are holding up so far. The only issue I'm having is with the separate wireless floodlight mount I ordered. I've had less then a month of use on the floodlight mount and I am already getting a low battery indicator. I'm hoping it's a software issue or just bad batteries that came with the mount. I returned the wired floodlight that came with this kit for the wireless floodlight mount and now I'm regretting that decision.

  • Christopher L.
    1.0 out of 5 stars Unreliable
    Reviewed in the United States on November 19, 2023
    Verified Purchase
    Half of the cameras stopped working within two weeks of purchase, no explanation why, just “disconnected”.

    I wrote a review of the doorbell as well, it was the most reliable of the system working (at most) between 30-40% of the time.

    These cameras are far worse, trust me, wireless security systems are not reliable or secure.

    These cameras were all mounted on the same level and less than 30ft of a super high end nighthawk router and we pay for high bandwidth internet service. Even with ideal installation, high bandwidth, and clear line of sight. These cameras are effectively worthless when it comes to home security.

    The best devices we had were the wired outdoor nest cameras, unfortunately they no longer sell the wired versions. They worked over 95% of the time and the video footage was a streaming 30 days (paid). These blink cameras provide hundreds of choppy useless clips that barely capture anything useful.

    I would say if you can’t afford more expensive systems to go ahead and buy, but based on our experience I think it’s better to have nothing than a non-functioning system that gives a false sense of security and you’re out hundreds of dollars anyway.

    Do not buy.
